https://www.coingecko.com/en/coins/komodo/developer#panel)

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> You fork what you want to work on, work on it and update your forked repo, get it so it works correctly, others try your fork to make sure it's good, help test, make additions, then they submit for merge, the code gets checked again to make sure it doesnt break things and then finally merged into komodo main branch.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> Otherwise you'd have tons of testing and additions that could force Komodo miners onto forks, or have security holes etc. The purpose is not to do testing on a chain with investors holding coins worth over $100MM. So go into discord, check out developer lounge and look at the repos they are working on BEFORE they push to Komodo main branch.
